{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UB3zDEkoJYLFqpEVqEaFzG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→name: add-field\n     2→description: Add a field to a Django model and propagate to admin, serializer, and factory\n     3→\n     4→variables:\n     5→  model_name:\n     6→    type: string\n     7→    required: true\n     8→    description: \"Name of the model class\"\n     9→  field_name:\n    10→    type: string\n    11→    required: true\n    12→    description: \"Name of the new field\"\n    13→  field_type:\n    14→    type: string\n    15→    required: true\n    16→    description: \"Django field type (e.g., CharField)\"\n    17→  field_args:\n    18→    type: string\n    19→    required: false\n    20→    default: \"\"\n    21→    description: \"Field arguments (e.g., max_length=20, default='bronze')\"\n    22→  factory_default:\n    23→    type: string\n    24→    required: false\n    25→    default: \"'test'\"\n    26→    description: \"Default value for the factory\"\n    27→\n    28→files:\n    29→  - template: templates/model_field.j2\n    30→    patch: \"models.py\"\n    31→    anchor:\n    32→      pattern: \"^class {{ model_name }}\"\n    33→      scope: class_body\n    34→      position: after_last_field\n    35→    skip_if: \"{{ field_name }}\"\n    36→\n    37→  - template: templates/admin_field.j2\n    38→    inject: \"admin.py\"\n    39→    after: 'list_display = \\['\n    40→    skip_if: \"{{ field_name }}\"\n    41→\n    42→  - template: templates/serializer_field.j2\n    43→    inject: \"serializers.py\"\n    44→    after: 'fields = \\['\n    45→    skip_if: \"{{ field_name }}\"\n    46→\n    47→  - template: templates/factory_field.j2\n    48→    patch: \"factories.py\"\n    49→    anchor:\n    50→      pattern: \"^class {{ model_name }}Factory\"\n    51→      scope: class_body\n    52→      position: after_last_field\n    53→    skip_if: \"{{ field_name }}\"\n    54→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"859b0f0c-d268-4e77-a857-edf812c507ed","uuid":"61dc2681-928e-4d48-828c-b279c89d0f1a"}
